WEBVTT

00:02.437 --> 00:06.789
♪ I've been watching ♪

00:06.832 --> 00:08.399
Wow.

00:08.443 --> 00:11.489
♪ All of my past repeating ♪

00:11.533 --> 00:15.754
♪ There's no ending ♪

00:15.798 --> 00:20.368
♪ And when I stop pretending ♪

00:20.411 --> 00:24.720
♪ See you standing ♪

00:24.763 --> 00:27.244
♪ Facing ♪

00:27.288 --> 00:31.770
♪ All mirrors are erasing ♪

00:31.814 --> 00:36.427
♪ Losing beauty ♪

00:36.471 --> 00:40.823
♪ At least at times it knew me ♪

00:45.480 --> 00:49.788
♪ At least at times it knew me ♪

00:49.832 --> 00:51.877
I missed you.

00:51.921 --> 00:54.663
Nick.

00:54.706 --> 00:59.450
♪ At least at times it knew me ♪

00:59.494 --> 01:01.496
[thudding]

01:03.541 --> 01:06.544
[door creaks open]

01:18.687 --> 01:20.645
[eerie breathing echoes]

01:20.689 --> 01:22.691
[thudding]

01:30.742 --> 01:31.700
[shrieks]

01:31.743 --> 01:33.571
[gasps]

01:33.615 --> 01:35.486
[exhales]

01:39.273 --> 01:40.926
NANCY:
Either Dead Lucy really wants me

01:40.970 --> 01:42.580
to check out what's in here

01:42.624 --> 01:44.756
or she's got
some pretty strong opinions

01:44.800 --> 01:46.758
about my love life.

01:46.802 --> 01:48.804
♪ ♪

02:14.656 --> 02:17.659
Mom was Lucy Sable's
guidance counselor?

02:21.663 --> 02:23.839
[buzzing]

02:25.667 --> 02:27.103
Dad.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.323
Hey, you.

02:29.366 --> 02:31.020
It's so good to see you.

02:31.063 --> 02:32.848
Yeah, you, too.

02:33.849 --> 02:34.980
[handcuffs click]

02:35.024 --> 02:36.634
You okay?

02:36.678 --> 02:38.288
Yeah. I'm okay.

02:38.332 --> 02:41.683
We're gonna get you out of here.
It's just, uh...

02:41.726 --> 02:44.729
All that stuff that I wrote
in my journal, it was just...

02:44.773 --> 02:46.992
They-they were just theories,
and they were wrong.

02:47.036 --> 02:49.038
And I am gonna fix this.

02:49.081 --> 02:51.171
Hey. I promise you,
I will fix it, because...

02:51.214 --> 02:53.129
Hey, hey. Can we just...

02:53.173 --> 02:54.739
Can we take a minute?

02:56.437 --> 02:58.917
I'm happy you're here.

03:01.703 --> 03:03.052
How are you?

03:03.095 --> 03:04.358
You look tired.

03:04.401 --> 03:06.316
I found a box of Mom's old files

03:06.360 --> 03:07.883
underneath the staircase.

03:07.926 --> 03:09.711
She was a guidance counselor
at Keene High?

03:09.754 --> 03:10.886
She never told me that.

03:10.929 --> 03:12.670
Old history, I guess.

03:12.714 --> 03:14.672
It was while she was getting
her master's.

03:14.716 --> 03:15.978
She had a folder for Lucy Sable.

03:16.021 --> 03:17.980
But it was empty.

03:18.023 --> 03:19.155
Do you know why?

03:19.199 --> 03:21.244
No.

03:21.288 --> 03:22.811
I don't.

03:22.854 --> 03:24.943
Your mom was meticulous
with her files.

03:24.987 --> 03:27.337
It's just I think
that whatever was supposed to be

03:27.381 --> 03:29.383
in that folder could lead us
to Lucy's real killer.

03:29.426 --> 03:31.211
Maybe there was something

03:31.254 --> 03:33.038
incriminating
in Lucy's transcript.

03:33.082 --> 03:35.432
Something that the Hudsons
wanted gone. Is there any chance

03:35.476 --> 03:37.304
that they could've gotten access
to Mom's stuff?

03:37.347 --> 03:39.219
Your mom and I
shared a home office.

03:39.262 --> 03:41.873
Everett came to see me there
occasionally.

03:41.917 --> 03:44.049
Maybe he took it. If he did,

03:44.093 --> 03:45.834
he would've destroyed it.

03:45.877 --> 03:48.837
I don't want you
getting involved.

03:48.880 --> 03:50.230
Okay.

03:50.273 --> 03:51.361
Then you get involved.

03:51.405 --> 03:53.276
Fight this.
Tell the cops

03:53.320 --> 03:55.017
that it was the Hudsons
who sent you to the cliffs

03:55.060 --> 03:56.105
the night Lucy died.

03:56.148 --> 03:57.367
I can't prove that.

03:57.411 --> 03:59.369
It would be their word
against mine,

03:59.413 --> 04:02.198
and my prints are on the knife.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.373
You know that they
could've paid somebody

04:03.417 --> 04:05.245
to plant your prints. Or maybe

04:05.288 --> 04:07.943
I did stumble across the knife
that night, and I just...

04:07.986 --> 04:09.901
I forgot about it
in all the confusion. Dad,

04:09.945 --> 04:11.425
stop second-guessing
your memory.

04:11.468 --> 04:14.210
We have to find the person
that actually did do this

04:14.254 --> 04:16.125
so that we can get you
out of here.

04:16.168 --> 04:18.170
Please.

04:18.214 --> 04:20.260
Let this go.

04:20.303 --> 04:23.350
You know me better than that.

04:23.393 --> 04:25.395
♪ ♪

04:35.449 --> 04:36.928
Hey, Owen.

04:36.972 --> 04:38.408
Uh, give me a call back.

04:38.452 --> 04:40.845
I'm working on this
"two birds, one stone" thing

04:40.889 --> 04:42.151
with my dad,

04:42.194 --> 04:45.502
and, also, I was
thinking of you.

04:49.158 --> 04:51.291
Glad I'm not the only one
who was running late.

04:51.334 --> 04:54.294
I didn't see Ace's car in
the parking lot, either.

04:54.337 --> 04:57.035
He's fishing with his dad,
and George is in a meeting.

04:57.079 --> 04:58.950
So we have a minute,
which is good,

04:58.994 --> 05:01.170
because I need to clear
my throat chakra.

05:01.213 --> 05:03.781
Some sort of disturbance
in the Force?

05:03.825 --> 05:05.348
No, Owen called.

05:05.392 --> 05:08.003
I'm having lunch
with Aunt Diana today.

05:08.046 --> 05:10.788
Going full Marvin.
Congratulations.

05:10.832 --> 05:12.137
I know.
[chuckles]

05:12.181 --> 05:14.183
It's exactly how
I manifested it.

05:14.226 --> 05:16.359
Unless I totally blow it.

05:16.403 --> 05:18.448
I-I could totally blow it.

05:18.492 --> 05:21.451
I-I... Aren't you in by
virtue of DNA?

05:21.495 --> 05:25.063
No. Genetics gets you
through the door.

05:25.107 --> 05:26.326
It's not like we were doing well

05:26.369 --> 05:27.457
before the rich
lady was murdered.

05:27.501 --> 05:28.545
All right, well,
have you seen the sales

05:28.589 --> 05:29.981
from the last two weeks?

05:30.025 --> 05:31.940
It's a Band-Aid
on a fire hydrant.

05:31.983 --> 05:33.420
Dawn, I can fix this.

05:36.466 --> 05:39.556
I'm putting The Bayside Claw
on the market.

05:39.600 --> 05:41.297
What?

05:43.255 --> 05:45.388
MAN: You're still working
at J. Dodd's and living there?

05:45.432 --> 05:47.216
Yeah. I like the commute.

05:47.259 --> 05:49.436
Mm-hmm. Well,
you got your GED.

05:49.479 --> 05:51.002
You got options.

05:51.046 --> 05:53.440
And here's the good news.

05:53.483 --> 05:57.182
This is the last time you're
gonna have to hear me say that.

05:57.226 --> 05:58.836
We have reached

05:58.880 --> 06:01.361
the end of our court-ordered
counseling sessions.

06:01.404 --> 06:03.188
After today, you're on your own.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.581
So...

06:04.625 --> 06:06.148
What is it you want?

06:06.191 --> 06:10.065
What if... I don't know, Keenan?

06:10.108 --> 06:11.936
Well, I hear Florida's nice.

06:11.980 --> 06:15.505
No. I'm not ready to
face my family yet.

06:15.549 --> 06:17.420
My parents are teachers,

06:17.464 --> 06:19.422
and my cousins
are in med school.

06:19.466 --> 06:21.859
And I'm the guy

06:21.903 --> 06:24.862
who spent two years in prison.

06:24.906 --> 06:27.517
If you don't quit looking
in the rearview mirror,

06:27.561 --> 06:29.563
you'll never change that.

06:41.270 --> 06:42.924
[bell jingles]
What... [sighs]

06:42.967 --> 06:44.491
I'll be back as soon as I can.

06:44.534 --> 06:45.622
Wait, seriously?

06:45.666 --> 06:48.103
We'll be waterfront condos
by then.

06:50.148 --> 06:53.413
Mr. Hudson, you need
to help my father.

06:55.153 --> 06:57.242
I have no idea
what you're talking about,

06:57.286 --> 06:59.244
though I admire your
allergy to pleasantries.

06:59.288 --> 07:01.551
My father's in jail because of
the money you wired him

07:01.595 --> 07:03.510
to clean up Lucy Sable's murder.

07:03.553 --> 07:06.295
Never hired Carson to
clean up a crime scene.

07:06.338 --> 07:08.384
You and I both know
he didn't do it.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.604
You have the leverage
to get him out of there.

07:10.647 --> 07:12.344
A phone call to a judge

07:12.388 --> 07:14.303
or the state police
is all it would take.

07:15.478 --> 07:17.132
Perhaps.

07:18.525 --> 07:20.962
You want something in return.

07:26.228 --> 07:28.926
Owen Marvin thinks I
had something to do

07:28.970 --> 07:31.494
with his Uncle Sebastian's
death on the Bonny Scot.

07:31.538 --> 07:33.104
He's spreading rumors

07:33.148 --> 07:35.542
that some artifacts from
the ship have resurfaced.

07:35.585 --> 07:38.501
But since the Bonny Scot's
cargo sank along with her,

07:38.545 --> 07:42.157
anything he has is counterfeit.

07:42.200 --> 07:45.160
Still, I can't have him
slandering my family

07:45.203 --> 07:49.686
by suggesting we've been
engaged in insurance fraud.

07:49.730 --> 07:51.383
Not to mention murder.

07:51.427 --> 07:53.690
I mean, the ship went down
with her crew, right?

07:53.734 --> 07:56.432
It was a tragic accident.

07:57.738 --> 08:01.219
Find out what Owen
thinks he has.

08:01.263 --> 08:03.004
Don't you have people

08:03.047 --> 08:05.006
that usually do
this kind of stuff for you?

08:05.049 --> 08:07.661
Yes, I do. And he's in jail.

08:07.704 --> 08:10.359
You want my help getting him out
or not?

08:12.361 --> 08:14.015
You know your way out.

08:19.194 --> 08:21.196
[eerie breathing echoes]

08:45.742 --> 08:47.744
[liquid dripping]

09:11.072 --> 09:13.074
[sighs]

09:28.219 --> 09:30.265
LISBETH:
So, you said your house is on this street?

09:30.308 --> 09:33.834
BESS:
I said my residence was.

09:33.877 --> 09:35.618
Voilà.

09:35.662 --> 09:38.360
Home sweet home.

09:39.927 --> 09:41.624
[dings]
BESS: Oh, I stole those.

09:41.668 --> 09:44.366
Yeah, when-when I get anxious,
I get klepto.

09:44.409 --> 09:46.324
Oh, don't arrest me.

09:46.368 --> 09:47.978
For what?

09:48.022 --> 09:51.329
Definitely did not just hear you
admit to petty theft.

09:54.332 --> 09:56.334
Tell me everything.

10:00.077 --> 10:04.386
Okay. I grew up
in Tower Hamlets,

10:04.429 --> 10:07.345
a rough neighborhood
in East London.

10:07.389 --> 10:08.695
That's where my dad's from.

10:08.738 --> 10:11.045
You don't have an accent. Oh, no.

10:11.088 --> 10:14.048
That does not go with the future
I'm manifesting for myself.

10:14.091 --> 10:18.400
Or maybe it's an opportunity
to embrace authenticity.

10:20.054 --> 10:22.099
I'm kind of a fan
of the Brits, myself.

10:23.318 --> 10:25.189
[British accent]:
Are you sure?

10:25.233 --> 10:27.801
[exhales]
Oh, yeah.
[chuckles]

10:27.844 --> 10:30.499
[laughs]

10:31.718 --> 10:33.763
So, when did you leave London?

10:33.807 --> 10:35.460
A year ago.

10:35.504 --> 10:40.030
I came here to be an Au pair
for a family in New Hampshire.

10:40.074 --> 10:42.424
But I got fired...

10:42.467 --> 10:44.992
for stealing.

10:45.035 --> 10:46.471
And...

10:46.515 --> 10:48.691
now I can't go back.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.867
My visa ran out
a few months ago.

10:50.911 --> 10:54.349
But I'm hoping, with
the Marvins' influence,

10:54.392 --> 10:56.786
they can get me a green card...

10:56.830 --> 10:58.788
if all goes well today.

10:58.832 --> 11:00.877
Hey. It will.

11:00.921 --> 11:02.879
Okay?

11:02.923 --> 11:05.012
You can get through lunch
with Diana.

11:05.055 --> 11:06.274
[chuckles]

11:08.276 --> 11:12.367
And as for me accepting you,

11:12.410 --> 11:14.195
that ship has totally sailed.

11:21.028 --> 11:23.247
GEORGE: You said,
if I ever needed something,

11:23.291 --> 11:25.249
you would help me, right?

11:25.293 --> 11:26.729
Right.

11:26.773 --> 11:28.165
Will you help The Claw for me?

11:29.558 --> 11:31.386
It's going under,
and it's the only thing I have

11:31.429 --> 11:32.779
paying my family's rent.

11:32.822 --> 11:34.302
Look, I have plans to bring
a new business,

11:34.345 --> 11:36.739
but I can't do that if they turn
this place into condos.

11:36.783 --> 11:39.263
Why don't you just get a job
somewhere else? Not an option.

11:39.307 --> 11:40.961
Between me and my mom,
other restaurants

11:41.004 --> 11:42.440
aren't exactly fans of the Fans.

11:42.484 --> 11:46.053
And neither is any other
place in town, really.

11:46.096 --> 11:47.837
Well... No, look.

11:47.881 --> 11:51.406
We just need $40,000 to catch up
with payroll and overdue bills.

11:51.449 --> 11:53.277
Then we can keep the lights on
for the next few months,

11:53.321 --> 11:55.062
while I get
this place going again.

11:55.105 --> 11:57.107
Look, and we'll pay you back,
with interest.

11:57.151 --> 12:00.110
I wish that I could, but I'm-I'm
working through some stuff

12:00.154 --> 12:01.938
with my family right now.

12:01.982 --> 12:04.201
I'm sorry.

12:05.420 --> 12:07.988
Hey. How goes
"Making a Marvin"?

12:08.031 --> 12:10.207
Trying not to freak out.

12:10.251 --> 12:12.035
[British accent]:
Failing.

12:12.079 --> 12:13.863
It's nice to hear the real you.

12:13.907 --> 12:15.778
Yeah, I'm giving her a go.

12:15.822 --> 12:18.346
Hey, is there any chance
Owen's gonna be at this lunch?

12:18.389 --> 12:20.391
He's not returning my calls.

12:20.435 --> 12:21.566
Why do you need him?

12:21.610 --> 12:23.307
Everett Hudson
wanted me to find out

12:23.351 --> 12:24.831
if Owen has anything on him.

12:24.874 --> 12:27.311
He claims he'll help get my
dad out of jail in return.

12:27.355 --> 12:29.226
I'm not gonna sell out Owen.

12:29.270 --> 12:31.228
I just think it could be helpful

12:31.272 --> 12:33.970
if Everett thinks that I am willing to.
Devious.

12:34.014 --> 12:35.189
I like it.

12:35.232 --> 12:37.147
Yeah, we should ask Owen
for help.

12:37.191 --> 12:39.280
You know, I actually keep
a running tab

12:39.323 --> 12:41.325
on the Marvins at all times.

12:41.369 --> 12:43.806
Not in a stalker way.

12:43.850 --> 12:45.416
I had to know
exactly where they were

12:45.460 --> 12:47.984
in order to avoid them
before I could present myself.

12:48.028 --> 12:49.333
Yeah, I'm, like,
a reverse stalker.

12:49.377 --> 12:51.031
When it comes to following

12:51.074 --> 12:52.510
people around without their
knowledge or consent,

12:52.554 --> 12:54.077
I am somewhat of a
repeat offender.

12:54.121 --> 12:55.949
This is true.

12:55.992 --> 12:59.953
Okay, so Owen should be
having his weekly trim.

12:59.996 --> 13:01.302
Done in 15 minutes.

13:03.217 --> 13:04.522
I'll drive.

13:04.566 --> 13:07.134
Okay.

13:07.177 --> 13:09.179
♪ ♪

13:15.664 --> 13:17.666
[line ringing]

13:19.581 --> 13:21.626
[cell phone ringing]

13:23.237 --> 13:24.847
BESS:
Guess he's not endgame

13:24.891 --> 13:26.240
after all.

13:26.283 --> 13:28.982
I am only disappointed
because of the task at hand.

13:29.025 --> 13:30.635
Yeah. You keep
telling yourself that.

13:30.679 --> 13:32.899
♪ ♪

13:46.347 --> 13:48.305
Why are you ducking my calls?

13:48.349 --> 13:50.307
Yeah. Is it
another girl?

13:50.351 --> 13:53.615
Oh, how could you put me
in the middle of this, Owen? No,

13:53.658 --> 13:55.138
no other girls but you two.

13:55.182 --> 13:56.923
Bess, I thought
you'd be getting ready

13:56.966 --> 13:58.272
for lunch with Diana.
No.

13:58.315 --> 14:00.143
I have exactly one hour,

14:00.187 --> 14:03.103
six minutes and 52 seconds.

14:04.452 --> 14:06.584
And I'm British, by the way.

14:06.628 --> 14:09.022
Okay.
Is this about the Bonny Scot?

14:09.065 --> 14:10.545
This is why I've
been avoiding you, Nancy.

14:10.588 --> 14:12.939
It's impossible
to keep anything from you.

14:14.288 --> 14:16.029
Come on, follow me.

14:19.510 --> 14:21.251
[knocking]

14:21.295 --> 14:22.905
Bashiir?

14:22.949 --> 14:25.125
I'm Owen. We spoke
on the phone earlier.

14:25.168 --> 14:26.691
You didn't mention
bringing others.

14:26.735 --> 14:28.215
Uh, sorry.

14:28.258 --> 14:31.000
Uh, these two are habitual
party crashers, but...

14:31.044 --> 14:32.480
they're on our side.

14:34.482 --> 14:37.137
[chain sliding, clacking]

14:38.529 --> 14:41.010
Bess, Nancy, this is Bashiir,

14:41.054 --> 14:43.404
sole survivor of the Bonny Scot.

14:51.760 --> 14:55.590
My family had a lobster-fishing
business in Mogadishu.

14:55.633 --> 14:57.635
The warlords seized it...

14:57.679 --> 14:59.724
and killed my parents.

15:00.725 --> 15:02.205
I fled.

15:02.249 --> 15:04.251
So sorry.

15:04.294 --> 15:05.948
[chuckles wryly]

15:05.992 --> 15:09.256
I met a man, Gabriel,
who could get me on a ship

15:09.299 --> 15:10.910
to the U.S.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.912
I paid him everything I had.

15:12.955 --> 15:15.218
Gabriel was one of my Uncle
Sebastian's partners in Turkey.

15:15.262 --> 15:18.091
He told me about Bashiir.
I stowed away

15:18.134 --> 15:21.659
aboard the Bonny Scott
when it was docked in Istanbul.

15:21.703 --> 15:23.879
It wasn't hard to hide.

15:23.923 --> 15:26.099
The shipping containers
were empty.

15:26.142 --> 15:29.667
Because the cargo never
made it on board the Bonny Scot.

15:31.278 --> 15:33.367
What happened
the night she sank?

15:33.410 --> 15:35.630
I don't like reliving it.

15:35.673 --> 15:37.371
OWEN:
Please.

15:37.414 --> 15:39.677
I just want to know what
happened to my uncle.

15:39.721 --> 15:43.246
I snuck up to the top deck
to look at the stars,

15:43.290 --> 15:45.640
and a bomb exploded below deck.

15:45.683 --> 15:48.121
How did you know
that it was a bomb?

15:48.164 --> 15:50.036
From the war.

15:50.079 --> 15:52.299
I know the sound.

15:52.342 --> 15:55.389
I was able to get
to the life raft.

15:55.432 --> 15:57.217
I was the only one.

15:57.260 --> 15:58.696
The fishing boat found me.

15:58.740 --> 16:00.829
They asked me
where to drop me off.

16:00.872 --> 16:02.657
I didn't know.

16:02.700 --> 16:04.659
The crew on the Bonny Scot

16:04.702 --> 16:07.009
talked about this place,
Horseshoe Bay,

16:07.053 --> 16:09.664
so I just said that.

16:09.707 --> 16:12.319
And... and you've been here
ever since?

16:12.362 --> 16:14.016
My plan was

16:14.060 --> 16:17.063
to claim asylum once I got here.

16:17.106 --> 16:20.109
But I was afraid
to come forward.

16:20.153 --> 16:22.720
I thought the authorities
wouldn't believe me.

16:22.764 --> 16:24.026
Or worse, they'd blame me.

16:24.070 --> 16:25.332
Why would they blame you?

16:25.375 --> 16:27.943
Because of where I'm from.

16:27.987 --> 16:30.859
People sometimes suspect
the worst

16:30.902 --> 16:33.427
when they hear
the words "Somali"

16:33.470 --> 16:35.429
or "undocumented."

16:35.472 --> 16:37.039
Maybe...

16:37.083 --> 16:40.173
we can help you with
your immigration status.

16:40.216 --> 16:41.957
OWEN:
If you can tell people

16:42.001 --> 16:43.306
what really happened.

16:43.350 --> 16:46.005
Look, I know
I should go to the police.

16:46.048 --> 16:47.745
I know that.

16:47.789 --> 16:51.097
But... I don't want
to have to leave.

16:51.140 --> 16:54.230
I've made a good life
fishing here.

16:54.274 --> 16:56.276
You ask me to risk
everything I have.

16:56.319 --> 16:57.712
I'm-I'm sorry.

16:57.755 --> 16:59.018
I cannot do it.

16:59.061 --> 17:00.932
NANCY:
Bashiir.

17:02.282 --> 17:04.284
How did you get
these water stains?

17:07.243 --> 17:09.158
You all have to go now.

17:09.202 --> 17:11.073
Please.

17:14.772 --> 17:16.513
We're gonna help him, right?

17:18.037 --> 17:19.995
He'd make it easier
if he were willing

17:20.039 --> 17:21.431
to come forward
with his testimony.

17:21.475 --> 17:23.085
We should help him anyway.

17:23.129 --> 17:24.217
We're the good guys.

17:24.260 --> 17:25.348
And...

17:25.392 --> 17:27.176
I know what it feels like

17:27.220 --> 17:29.352
to come here,
try and make a life,

17:29.396 --> 17:31.963
terrified that one day
you'll be forced to leave.

17:32.007 --> 17:33.095
[cell phone chimes]

17:33.139 --> 17:34.488
[Bess sighs]

17:34.531 --> 17:37.317
I'm gonna be late for lunch.

17:37.360 --> 17:39.406
But I will grab a Lyft...

17:39.449 --> 17:41.451
and let you two talk.

17:42.974 --> 17:45.760
So you were never gonna tell
me you found a survivor?

17:45.803 --> 17:47.457
Was I supposed to?

17:47.501 --> 17:49.372
I care about getting justice
for the Bonny Scot, too.

17:49.416 --> 17:52.375
Yeah, I know. But you've got
your own stuff going on.

17:52.419 --> 17:54.116
I think my dad being in jail
qualifies

17:54.160 --> 17:55.335
as more than just "stuff."

17:55.378 --> 17:57.076
Absolutely.

17:57.119 --> 17:59.208
And it deserves
that insanely reckless,

17:59.252 --> 18:01.906
singularly focused drive
that makes you great.

18:01.950 --> 18:04.170
Oof. Why doesn't that feel
like a compliment?

18:04.213 --> 18:05.954
It's recognition.

18:05.997 --> 18:07.956
We both go after what we want,
and we usually get it,

18:07.999 --> 18:10.219
even if it means other things
fall by the wayside.

18:10.263 --> 18:11.568
Other people, too.

18:14.484 --> 18:16.486
[door opens, footsteps approach]

18:18.358 --> 18:19.446
Ah...

18:19.489 --> 18:21.839
I live for your tuna melts.

18:21.883 --> 18:23.798
[chuckles]
Pretty sad.

18:23.841 --> 18:25.974
Also, I'm sorry, but...

18:26.017 --> 18:27.932
you have to pay
for your food now.

18:27.976 --> 18:29.151
Everything okay?

18:29.195 --> 18:32.502
The Claw's in some serious
financial trouble.

18:32.546 --> 18:34.025
I'm sorry.

18:34.069 --> 18:36.506
I know how important
this job is to you.

18:36.550 --> 18:38.813
It's not just a job.

18:38.856 --> 18:41.032
My grandparents supplied
the fish for The Claw

18:41.076 --> 18:42.860
until my mom messed that up.

18:42.904 --> 18:44.993
Dawn didn't hold that
against me.

18:45.036 --> 18:48.083
When my mom couldn't feed us,
they always did.

18:50.868 --> 18:54.133
I carved my name into every
single one of these tables.

18:54.176 --> 18:57.353
I mean, this place is more
of a home than my actual home.

18:58.354 --> 19:00.443
Sorry to get all gross about it.

19:00.487 --> 19:02.053
No, don't be sorry.

19:02.097 --> 19:03.533
Hey...

19:03.577 --> 19:07.363
I've never had a connection
to anything like that.

19:09.365 --> 19:11.585
How you gonna save this place?

19:11.628 --> 19:14.327
I have ideas
for next summer, but...

19:14.370 --> 19:16.894
we're a seafood restaurant
and a vacation town,

19:16.938 --> 19:19.027
and it's off-season, so...

19:19.070 --> 19:21.986
Maybe... have a party.

19:22.030 --> 19:23.249
Hmm? Remind
the locals

19:23.292 --> 19:24.380
lobster's good all year.

19:24.424 --> 19:27.078
"Still Summer at The Bayside Claw."

19:27.122 --> 19:28.210
I'll help.

19:28.254 --> 19:29.342
[chuckles softly]

19:29.385 --> 19:31.082
Can't pay you.

19:31.126 --> 19:32.867
No. I could
use a project.

19:32.910 --> 19:34.347
You know, plus...

19:34.390 --> 19:36.349
I work for tuna melts.

19:36.392 --> 19:38.351
[laughs]

19:38.394 --> 19:40.570
Yeah, you got
some real problems.

19:40.614 --> 19:42.355
[chuckles]

19:42.398 --> 19:44.922
♪ ♪

19:51.102 --> 19:54.062
DIANA:
Your mother was a rebellious spirit.

19:54.105 --> 19:56.369
Pity she kept you from us.

19:56.412 --> 19:59.110
There's a place for you
in this family, Bess,

19:59.154 --> 20:00.460
should you want it.

20:00.503 --> 20:02.244
I do. I do.

20:02.288 --> 20:03.898
I mean...

20:03.941 --> 20:05.900
that would be wonderful.

20:05.943 --> 20:09.469
Of course, being a Marvin means
doing things the Marvin way.

20:09.512 --> 20:11.079
Is there any other way?

20:11.122 --> 20:13.081
Well, you can help
with the family business, too.

20:13.124 --> 20:15.431
Mergers and acquisitions.

20:15.475 --> 20:18.173
I do like buying things.

20:18.217 --> 20:22.308
Bess, I want you to have lunch
with Amaya Alston,

20:22.351 --> 20:25.267
heiress to the largest
precious minerals distributor

20:25.311 --> 20:26.660
in North America.

20:26.703 --> 20:28.618
I would love to meet her. We've been wanting

20:28.662 --> 20:31.969
to get into business
with the Alstons for years.

20:32.013 --> 20:33.536
And she's about your age,

20:33.580 --> 20:35.669
so you'd have plenty
to talk about.

20:35.712 --> 20:38.106
And I think

20:38.149 --> 20:39.455
you'd like her a lot.

20:39.499 --> 20:41.414
Are you worried

20:41.457 --> 20:44.286
about your girlfriend, Lisbeth?

20:45.722 --> 20:47.376
Don't be.

20:47.420 --> 20:48.943
My hope is...

20:48.986 --> 20:51.380
that Amaya will simply become
a mentor to you

20:51.424 --> 20:53.295
in the world of business.

20:53.339 --> 20:56.951
And as for Lisbeth,
well, there's no issue

20:56.994 --> 20:59.606
with having fun
with the drivers, bodyguards,

20:59.649 --> 21:02.130
pool boys or girls.

21:02.173 --> 21:05.220
Your mother certainly did.

21:06.700 --> 21:10.269
But... Marvins
don't marry drivers.

21:11.400 --> 21:12.967
Bess,

21:13.010 --> 21:15.274
clear you schedule for dinner
tomorrow night.

21:18.364 --> 21:20.191
[bells jingle]

21:20.235 --> 21:22.193
GEORGE:
Hey, hey, hey,

21:22.237 --> 21:24.152
where did those come from?
We can't afford that.

21:24.195 --> 21:26.459
Moonstone Castle Brewery
donated 'em.

21:26.502 --> 21:29.288
I convinced 'em to do
a cross-promotional thing.

21:29.331 --> 21:31.420
Acceptable.

21:31.464 --> 21:33.770
[sighs]

21:38.209 --> 21:39.298
[laughs]

21:39.341 --> 21:40.342
Want to add your name?

21:41.387 --> 21:42.344
Really?

21:42.388 --> 21:44.346
You earned it.

21:46.261 --> 21:47.654
But just one.

21:47.697 --> 21:49.133
Okay.

21:50.613 --> 21:52.311
Huh.

21:54.400 --> 21:55.792
Hey.

21:58.186 --> 22:00.319
Use this.

22:04.453 --> 22:06.194
[grunts]

22:08.152 --> 22:09.632
[bells jingle]

22:09.676 --> 22:12.374
Whoa. What's all of... Ow. Ow.

22:12.418 --> 22:13.593
...um, this?

22:13.636 --> 22:15.551
- GEORGE: Hey.
- Hey.

22:15.595 --> 22:17.553
I'm gonna go check
on the clam delivery.

22:18.598 --> 22:20.556
Uh...

22:20.600 --> 22:23.385
"Still Summer at the Bayside Claw."

22:23.429 --> 22:26.519
Yeah, George's big event
to get in more traffic.

22:26.562 --> 22:29.260
Well, we could certainly use it.
[sighs]

22:31.785 --> 22:33.047
You okay?

22:33.090 --> 22:34.396
Am I a bad person?

22:34.440 --> 22:36.050
No.

22:36.093 --> 22:38.444
Where is this coming from?

22:38.487 --> 22:42.404
Everett Hudson offered to
help get my dad out of jail.

22:42.448 --> 22:44.798
In exchange for...? Spying on Owen and seeing

22:44.841 --> 22:46.800
if he has any leads
on the Bonny Scot.

22:46.843 --> 22:50.064
And I'm guessing he does. He found a survivor, Nick.

22:50.107 --> 22:52.414
This guy Bashiir... he stowed
away on the Bonny Scot,

22:52.458 --> 22:54.068
and he escaped as it sank.

22:54.111 --> 22:55.461
And before you say anything,

22:55.504 --> 22:57.288
I'm not gonna give
him to Everett.

22:57.332 --> 22:58.812
I'm not a monster.

22:58.855 --> 23:01.815
No, you're not.
Just... selfish and cutthroat

23:01.858 --> 23:04.252
and willing to step over
anybody to get what I want.

23:04.295 --> 23:06.646
Why are you beating yourself up
if you're not gonna do it?

23:08.169 --> 23:10.084
You're thinking about doing it?

23:10.127 --> 23:11.564
I don't want Bashiir
to get hurt.

23:11.607 --> 23:14.088
Okay. And if he didn't get hurt?

23:14.131 --> 23:17.570
If you went to Everett and you
negotiated a scenario where

23:17.613 --> 23:20.747
Bashiir is safe
and your dad is free?

23:20.790 --> 23:23.750
Then the Hudsons get away with
murdering 12 innocent people.

23:23.793 --> 23:25.795
A bad person
wouldn't care about that.

23:25.839 --> 23:28.450
Maybe a good person

23:28.494 --> 23:31.758
does their best to help
as many people as possible.

23:31.801 --> 23:34.325
And I've seen your best, Nancy.

23:34.369 --> 23:36.676
There is nothing like it.

23:42.725 --> 23:44.248
Um... [clears throat]

23:44.292 --> 23:46.120
What does...
what does Bashiir want?

23:46.163 --> 23:47.643
He's really scared

23:47.687 --> 23:50.864
of being deported, but
there's something else, too.

23:50.907 --> 23:55.521
His apartment... it's-it's filled
with this oozing water damage.

23:55.564 --> 23:57.261
But it smells like the sea.

23:57.305 --> 23:58.741
It's not normal.

23:58.785 --> 24:00.700
You mentioned Dead Lucy
left seawater behind,

24:00.743 --> 24:03.485
and she died in the water.

24:03.529 --> 24:05.356
Think he's being haunted?

24:05.400 --> 24:07.750
I mean, he did survive
something horrific.

24:10.797 --> 24:12.799
We should go and visit him.

24:14.844 --> 24:16.846
And we should go right now.

24:16.890 --> 24:18.935
Yep.
Okay.

24:21.721 --> 24:24.288
All right,
200 clams ready to shuck.

24:25.681 --> 24:27.770
[door closes, bells jingle]

24:27.814 --> 24:29.816
Guess I'll just shuck myself.

24:32.775 --> 24:34.864
Bashiir?

24:34.908 --> 24:37.214
It's Nancy from before.

24:38.694 --> 24:40.566
What the...?

24:46.397 --> 24:48.182
Bashiir?

24:48.225 --> 24:49.531
BASHIIR:
Help!

24:50.706 --> 24:53.709
[Bashiir screaming]

24:54.797 --> 24:56.277
Bashiir?

24:56.320 --> 24:58.584
Bashiir? Bashiir?

24:58.627 --> 25:00.499
Oh, my God, it's the Bonny Scot.

25:00.542 --> 25:02.631
This must be what happened.

25:02.675 --> 25:04.894
Help! Help!

25:04.938 --> 25:07.201
I have to save them!
MAN: Hurry up!

25:07.244 --> 25:09.333
[grunting]
Hurry up!

25:09.377 --> 25:11.510
[people yelling]

25:11.553 --> 25:13.599
[grunting]

25:13.642 --> 25:16.340
[panicking yelling]

25:16.384 --> 25:18.473
Oh, no.

25:18.517 --> 25:20.214
[loud thud]

25:20.257 --> 25:22.216
[yelling]

25:22.259 --> 25:24.305
[yelling stops]
[exhales sharply]

25:24.348 --> 25:25.785
Forgive me.

25:34.533 --> 25:36.535
[water dripping]

25:40.277 --> 25:42.976
Does this happen every night?

25:43.019 --> 25:44.455
For the past three weeks.

25:44.499 --> 25:46.980
Since our séance.

25:47.023 --> 25:49.548
The Roman burial coins
must have woken up the ghosts

25:49.591 --> 25:51.332
of the Bonny Scot'screw.

25:51.375 --> 25:53.639
I've tried to stay at a hotel.

25:53.682 --> 25:56.250
It happens everywhere I go.

25:56.293 --> 25:59.383
It's because I-I...
I couldn't save them.

25:59.427 --> 26:01.037
[crying]

26:02.386 --> 26:04.519
Hey, hey, hey, I've...

26:04.563 --> 26:06.652
I've made mistakes in my life.

26:08.218 --> 26:11.526
And-and the guilt
has been so big that...

26:11.570 --> 26:13.659
I thought it would crush me.

26:15.051 --> 26:17.314
That shame doesn't
make things better.

26:17.358 --> 26:19.665
It just stops you
from moving forward.

26:19.708 --> 26:21.492
I want to move forward.

26:21.536 --> 26:24.670
And I'm... I'm sure
that feels impossible

26:24.713 --> 26:26.367
in your situation.

26:28.412 --> 26:30.414
I know about being haunted.

26:31.590 --> 26:35.115
Figuratively and...
literally.

26:36.159 --> 26:38.379
So, if you feel

26:38.422 --> 26:40.468
like you owe something
to these crew members,

26:40.511 --> 26:43.036
then help us
get justice for them.

26:43.079 --> 26:45.691
Will it make the hauntings stop?

26:45.734 --> 26:49.042
I-I truly believe that it will.

26:49.085 --> 26:50.652
Okay.

26:50.696 --> 26:52.219
[sniffles]

26:52.262 --> 26:53.568
Okay.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.614
I want to show you something.

27:05.275 --> 27:07.582
Oh, my God. Nick.

27:07.626 --> 27:09.062
Are those...

27:09.105 --> 27:11.368
bomb fragments? That's how I knew

27:11.412 --> 27:13.501
the explosion was no accident.

27:15.111 --> 27:17.679
I used this as a shield
when the fire broke out.

27:17.723 --> 27:20.508
The bomb must have been hidden
inside that trunk.

27:22.466 --> 27:24.120
So what do we do with it now?

27:26.209 --> 27:28.081
RYAN: Why do you want to meet with me

27:28.124 --> 27:29.691
when you already sat down
with my father?

27:29.735 --> 27:31.693
I have something
to run past you.

27:31.737 --> 27:33.434
Hypothetically,

27:33.477 --> 27:36.089
if I were to give Everett
something on Owen Marvin,

27:36.132 --> 27:37.743
do you think I could trust him?

27:37.786 --> 27:39.745
If my father gave you
his word, yes.

27:39.788 --> 27:42.095
But, Nancy,
it's not gonna end there.

27:42.138 --> 27:44.750
If he wants dirt on Owen,
he's got professionals.

27:44.793 --> 27:47.448
Why-why does he call
a college dropout?

27:47.491 --> 27:49.189
I didn't drop out.
I never applied.

27:49.232 --> 27:51.582
It's different.
And I went to him.

27:51.626 --> 27:53.323
Only, it doesn't matter.

27:53.367 --> 27:55.325
Well, I am out of options.

27:55.369 --> 27:58.285
Unless, of course,
you would be willing to help.

27:58.328 --> 28:00.200
[laughs]

28:00.243 --> 28:03.856
I may have my issues
with my father,

28:03.899 --> 28:07.294
but...

28:07.337 --> 28:10.123
I know well enough

28:10.166 --> 28:12.821
not to get involved
when he's in play.

28:14.388 --> 28:16.607
[door closes, engine starts]

28:16.651 --> 28:20.655
♪ Day after day... ♪

28:20.699 --> 28:23.571
[bells jingle]

28:23.614 --> 28:25.616
[song continues playing]

28:26.617 --> 28:28.837
[scoffs]

28:30.273 --> 28:32.798
Were you up all night?

28:34.451 --> 28:38.151
Oh, I... I didn't know you
were gonna keep working.

28:38.194 --> 28:40.588
You didn't ask.
You just left.

28:42.285 --> 28:44.505
I'm good.

28:44.548 --> 28:47.290
Are... we good?

28:47.334 --> 28:49.336
Sure. I just have
a lot to get done.

28:49.379 --> 28:51.730
Hey, don't push me away
just 'cause I want to help.

28:51.773 --> 28:53.688
You call this helping?

28:53.732 --> 28:55.690
I call it hiding behind
everyone else's problems.

28:55.734 --> 28:57.300
You broke up with Nancy,

28:57.344 --> 28:59.172
yet you drop everything
when she needs you.

28:59.215 --> 29:01.435
No. We had to get
to this guy's place

29:01.478 --> 29:03.524
before a certain time.
Mm-hmm.

29:03.567 --> 29:06.527
And... he could help us
take down the Hudsons.

29:06.570 --> 29:08.355
For Tiffany. Exactly.

29:08.398 --> 29:10.183
You make everyone else
your project.

29:10.226 --> 29:12.751
Look, you've got
a bunch of money.

29:12.794 --> 29:15.318
Why don't you go find
a project of your own?

29:18.713 --> 29:20.367
EVERETT:
Thanks for accepting

29:20.410 --> 29:22.586
our invitation.
It's been too long.

29:22.630 --> 29:23.892
Has it? And I was thinking

29:23.936 --> 29:25.807
it could have been
a little bit longer.

29:25.851 --> 29:28.375
Oh, man, I wish I still drank.

29:28.418 --> 29:31.247
So, is this your ticket
to the Alston family?

29:31.291 --> 29:32.901
She is darling.

29:32.945 --> 29:34.729
Bess is so much more than that.

29:34.773 --> 29:38.385
And it's good to keep family
close, what with someone

29:38.428 --> 29:41.344
going after Tiffany's
poor little sister.

29:41.388 --> 29:43.825
Dirty cop.
He'll pay for what he did.

29:43.869 --> 29:45.740
I think you've paid him enough.

29:45.784 --> 29:47.960
You don't think
your family has skeletons?

29:49.265 --> 29:51.224
Ask your aunt about Mirror Bay.

29:51.267 --> 29:53.704
Make no mistake,
if you come after us,

29:53.748 --> 29:55.968
any destruction
will be mutually assured.

29:56.011 --> 29:58.405
If you're done
threatening my nephew, Everett,

29:58.448 --> 29:59.754
can you pass the salt?
[doorbell rings]

29:59.798 --> 30:01.582
My soup is a bit bland.

30:01.625 --> 30:03.540
[door opens]

30:03.584 --> 30:05.238
I need to speak with Everett.

30:05.281 --> 30:06.717
What are you
doing here? Nancy?

30:06.761 --> 30:07.893
Uh...

30:07.936 --> 30:09.459
You can step into my office.

30:09.503 --> 30:11.244
Is this why

30:11.287 --> 30:13.420
I haven't been able to
reach our new friend?

30:13.463 --> 30:15.378
Everett's gonna
help free my dad.

30:15.422 --> 30:16.902
What's going on here?

30:16.945 --> 30:19.600
Owen found a survivor
of the Bonny Scot.

30:27.913 --> 30:30.741
Let's get this sorted out.

30:30.785 --> 30:34.049
Well, dinner is getting cold.

30:34.093 --> 30:36.182
And so what if
there's a survivor?

30:36.225 --> 30:39.141
He can prove that your family
sabotaged the Bonny Scot,

30:39.185 --> 30:40.839
killing the crew
and my Uncle Sebastian

30:40.882 --> 30:42.405
to keep the artifacts
for yourselves.

30:42.449 --> 30:43.754
CELIA:
Are you accusing us

30:43.798 --> 30:45.365
of murdering 12 people

30:45.408 --> 30:47.062
for insurance money?

30:47.106 --> 30:49.282
DIANA:
Her shocked and offended face.

30:49.325 --> 30:51.066
She's been honing it
for decades.

30:51.110 --> 30:54.504
Please. The payout
would have been pennies

30:54.548 --> 30:57.377
compared to what we would have
made had Sebastian lived.

30:57.420 --> 30:59.770
His death set back
both our companies.

30:59.814 --> 31:01.772
Billion-dollar deals fell apart.

31:01.816 --> 31:04.340
Maybe it was less about business

31:04.384 --> 31:06.473
and more about Everett wanting

31:06.516 --> 31:09.476
to kill Sebastian
for diddling you,

31:09.519 --> 31:11.434
Celia.
[clears throat]

31:11.478 --> 31:13.828
Mother? Oh, my goodness.

31:13.872 --> 31:15.308
NANCY:
The survivor has

31:15.351 --> 31:18.354
physical evidence...
pieces of the actual bomb.

31:18.398 --> 31:20.530
Which he could have
gotten anywhere.

31:20.574 --> 31:22.619
He knew the shipping containers
were empty.

31:22.663 --> 31:24.839
And he had a witness
that helped him get on board.

31:26.449 --> 31:28.495
How much
to make this all go away?

31:28.538 --> 31:31.193
Green card
and a nice retirement package

31:31.237 --> 31:32.412
for Bashiir.

31:32.455 --> 31:33.892
I can do that.

31:33.935 --> 31:36.111
Plus a new identity
and a relocation

31:36.155 --> 31:38.809
someplace the Marvins
can never find him.

31:38.853 --> 31:41.334
Let's say... two million?

31:42.770 --> 31:45.294
That'll work.

31:45.338 --> 31:47.209
Bashiir's account number.

31:50.256 --> 31:52.736
Ms. Drew,
you certainly are

31:52.780 --> 31:54.390
your father's daughter.

31:56.175 --> 31:58.699
Thanks for coming. Enjoy the party.

32:00.353 --> 32:02.355
LISBETH:
Everyone, please stay seated.

32:03.356 --> 32:04.705
Everett Hudson,

32:04.748 --> 32:06.228
you are under arrest for fraud,

32:06.272 --> 32:08.361
racketeering
and 12 counts of murder.

32:08.404 --> 32:11.451
The account you transferred
that money into... it's ours.

32:12.539 --> 32:14.280
Wait, hold up, hold up.

32:14.323 --> 32:16.630
You're a cop? I think it's called
a sting, Ryan.

32:16.673 --> 32:19.328
Looks like I won't be able to
help your father after all.

32:19.372 --> 32:20.808
I think we'll muddle through
without you.

32:20.851 --> 32:22.853
How could you let this happen?

32:22.897 --> 32:25.160
I should have left
after I found the proof

32:25.204 --> 32:27.206
of your affair with Sebastian.

32:29.208 --> 32:30.383
♪ ♪

32:52.318 --> 32:54.711
NANCY:
The missing contents of Lucy's file.

32:54.755 --> 32:56.975
Everett did take it.

33:02.023 --> 33:03.764
[sighs]

33:05.070 --> 33:07.898
Hey. Nice work.

33:07.942 --> 33:09.683
Hey. Thanks.

33:09.726 --> 33:12.077
Uh, you, too.
Thanks for the help.

33:12.120 --> 33:15.036
Yeah, faking a fight with you is
almost as fun as a real fight.

33:15.080 --> 33:17.169
[chuckles]

33:17.212 --> 33:18.387
We owe you.
Eh.

33:18.431 --> 33:19.736
Consider us even.

33:19.780 --> 33:21.390
For the coins.

33:21.434 --> 33:23.001
And you're gonna help Bashiir.

33:23.044 --> 33:24.741
Yeah, I'm financing
his lobster operation,

33:24.785 --> 33:27.701
and I hired the best immigration
lawyer on the East Coast.

33:27.744 --> 33:29.964
Now, that seems very fair.

33:33.750 --> 33:35.752
♪ ♪

33:43.760 --> 33:46.067
Like I said.

33:46.111 --> 33:49.070
We go after what we
want, and we get it.

33:51.116 --> 33:53.988
If you'd been me
and-and handing over Bashiir

33:54.032 --> 33:55.990
meant saving your family,
would you have done it?

33:56.034 --> 33:57.992
Uh, I-I don't know.

33:58.036 --> 34:00.212
It's a good thing you thought
of another alternative.

34:02.257 --> 34:04.433
Hey, can I finally take you out?

34:04.477 --> 34:06.479
To celebrate?

34:09.960 --> 34:11.832
Uh, I'd like to.

34:13.138 --> 34:15.140
But I can't.

34:17.142 --> 34:19.100
[sighs]

34:21.233 --> 34:22.886
Is this about Nick?

34:22.930 --> 34:24.932
It's not always about a guy.

34:28.153 --> 34:29.806
CELIA:
Your father will be out

34:29.850 --> 34:31.286
by the next
shareholders' meeting.

34:31.330 --> 34:33.332
Is that what you want?

34:34.768 --> 34:36.204
He's the head of this family,

34:36.248 --> 34:40.208
and, like it or not,
he steers our ship.

34:40.252 --> 34:43.429
He murdered Sebastian
for payback.

34:43.472 --> 34:46.214
11 men were collateral damage.

34:46.258 --> 34:48.956
Police do not have
proof of that.

34:50.958 --> 34:54.092
Well, I have a Grecian urn
from the Bonny Scot.

34:54.135 --> 34:56.094
Is that proof enough?

34:56.137 --> 34:59.053
Oh, you wouldn't.

34:59.097 --> 35:02.100
This family has drifted
off course, Mother.

35:04.102 --> 35:07.105
I think it's time
I steer this ship.

35:08.106 --> 35:09.890
♪ When I was a boy ♪

35:09.933 --> 35:12.849
♪ I learned not to cry... ♪

35:15.156 --> 35:17.115
Ooh, all right, Picasso.

35:17.158 --> 35:19.465
♪ I learned how to rhyme... ♪

35:21.249 --> 35:23.773
I'll be right back with
your drinks in a moment, okay?

35:23.817 --> 35:25.949
♪ This ribbon of mine... ♪

35:25.993 --> 35:27.212
How are the clams?

35:27.255 --> 35:28.909
[chuckles]
Great.

35:28.952 --> 35:31.085
Thank you. Thank you, guys.

35:31.129 --> 35:33.261
Get a button.
Thanks.

35:33.305 --> 35:35.263
Oh! Hi, Dawn.

35:35.307 --> 35:37.309
Welcome to The Claw.

35:38.310 --> 35:40.050
I-I... I love the party.

35:40.094 --> 35:41.878
It's gonna be a weekly thing.

35:43.924 --> 35:46.187
I was right about
listing this place.

35:46.231 --> 35:48.320
Got a call an hour ago
with a bite.

35:49.843 --> 35:51.801
I wanted to give you
the heads-up.

35:51.845 --> 35:54.064
I'm taking whatever they offer.

35:54.108 --> 35:56.415
I'm sorry.

36:06.686 --> 36:07.991
Stressful dinner, huh?

36:08.035 --> 36:10.516
Oh, you have no idea.

36:10.559 --> 36:11.821
[both chuckle]

36:11.865 --> 36:13.649
I really like that you're
keeping the accent.

36:13.693 --> 36:14.998
Thanks.
Mm-hmm.

36:15.042 --> 36:16.652
Yeah, you...

36:16.696 --> 36:19.307
were pretty amazing tonight.

36:19.351 --> 36:22.658
Well, I'm glad you think so.

36:22.702 --> 36:25.313
Because I am...

36:25.357 --> 36:28.664
maybe, kind of, sort of...

36:28.708 --> 36:31.014
[takes a deep breath]

36:31.058 --> 36:32.494
...falling in love with you,

36:32.538 --> 36:35.541
Bess Turani Marvin.

36:38.544 --> 36:40.502
Well...

36:40.546 --> 36:45.072
I'm a little, sort of
falling, too.

36:48.467 --> 36:50.512
♪ ♪

37:10.097 --> 37:12.099
[cell phone vibrating]

37:13.753 --> 37:15.711
What is it?

37:15.755 --> 37:17.757
I'll deal with it tomorrow.

37:20.150 --> 37:21.761
[balloon pops]

37:27.636 --> 37:29.464
Hey, what's up?

37:29.508 --> 37:32.467
Figured you'd be
on cloud nine right now.

37:33.860 --> 37:36.079
Dawn's selling The Claw. To who?

37:36.123 --> 37:39.126
Oh, I thought
I was the only inquiry.

37:41.433 --> 37:43.391
You're the one who inquired?

37:43.435 --> 37:45.959
O-Okay, um...

37:46.002 --> 37:48.483
I was gonna run it by you

37:48.527 --> 37:50.920
before I made
a real, actual offer.

37:50.964 --> 37:52.966
Like you said,
I have a lot of money.

37:53.009 --> 37:56.012
- Okay, but you can't just go
and buy me a restaurant.
- Whoa.

37:56.056 --> 37:59.407
[chuckles]:
I wasn't gonna buy it for you.

37:59.451 --> 38:01.627
We could split it.

38:01.670 --> 38:04.020
I'll loan you the money for
half, and when we make a profit,

38:04.064 --> 38:06.545
you can pay me back. Nick, no.

38:06.588 --> 38:08.460
Okay, I didn't ask you for
a loan, 'cause I didn't

38:08.503 --> 38:09.939
want you to put a
target on your back

38:09.983 --> 38:11.593
by cashing the bonds
Tiffany left you.

38:11.637 --> 38:14.770
Okay, the bonds are untraceable
if you use them right.

38:14.814 --> 38:18.644
I can give Dawn, like,
$400,000 worth of them.

38:18.687 --> 38:21.168
She'd settle for way less.

38:21.211 --> 38:23.170
I've been putting off
thinking about my future.

38:25.041 --> 38:26.652
Just...

38:26.695 --> 38:29.655
taking it day by day because...

38:29.698 --> 38:31.874
I didn't know what I wanted.

38:34.268 --> 38:37.140
But something like this...

38:37.184 --> 38:38.272
I can get behind.

38:40.100 --> 38:42.145
Also, our party was a hit.

38:42.189 --> 38:43.799
You and I make a great team.

38:43.843 --> 38:46.149
Uh, well, I did most
of the work, so...

38:46.193 --> 38:49.283
And that's why I need you.
What do you say?

38:56.856 --> 38:58.858
You want to finish
what you started?

39:03.515 --> 39:04.994
NANCY:
Thought I'd do anything

39:05.038 --> 39:07.562
to get you out of there,
but I just couldn't

39:07.606 --> 39:08.650
turn Bashiir over to Everett.

39:08.694 --> 39:09.999
CARSON:
You did the right thing.

39:10.043 --> 39:12.480
I just wish
you hadn't gotten involved.

39:12.524 --> 39:13.829
He'll come after you for this.

39:13.873 --> 39:15.222
I figured this was the only way

39:15.265 --> 39:16.876
to get you to abandon
your non-tactic

39:16.919 --> 39:18.181
of just sitting in there

39:18.225 --> 39:20.053
and letting people think
you're guilty.

39:20.096 --> 39:21.837
Nancy, please listen to me.

39:21.881 --> 39:23.926
Since you won't stand up to
the Hudsons to protect yourself,

39:23.970 --> 39:25.841
I'm hoping you will do it
to protect me.

39:25.885 --> 39:28.844
You're taking your life
in your hands.

39:28.888 --> 39:31.717
No. I'm putting it in yours.

39:31.760 --> 39:34.110
Because I need my dad back.

39:41.553 --> 39:43.816
I'll call my lawyer.

39:43.859 --> 39:47.863
I can't prove anything
about Lucy, but...

39:50.866 --> 39:52.912
There are things I know
about the Hudsons.

39:52.955 --> 39:56.089
Things I could leverage
for a plea deal.

39:56.132 --> 39:57.873
It's at least a place to start.

39:57.917 --> 40:00.093
Thanks, Dad.

40:00.136 --> 40:02.051
I love you.

40:02.095 --> 40:04.097
["Moon Call" by Diamond Thug playing]

40:06.099 --> 40:08.101
I love you, too.

40:14.237 --> 40:16.239
♪ ♪

40:24.291 --> 40:26.946
♪ I was left waiting ♪

40:26.989 --> 40:30.166
♪ Out for the day ♪

40:30.210 --> 40:32.560
♪ Keeping in trouble ♪

40:32.604 --> 40:35.911
♪ And keeping at bay ♪

40:35.955 --> 40:41.003
♪ If I live by the quiet light ♪

40:41.047 --> 40:43.745
♪ Then I may learn ♪
[watch beeping]

40:43.789 --> 40:46.313
♪ How to play the game ♪

40:46.356 --> 40:51.231
♪ Alone ♪

40:53.320 --> 40:57.672
♪ Alone... ♪
[laughing]

41:06.159 --> 41:08.857
[sighs]
Okay.

41:08.901 --> 41:11.338
"Celia's spreading rumors about me.

41:11.381 --> 41:14.646
My mom's gonna kill me if she finds out.

41:14.689 --> 41:17.300
You don't understand.

41:17.344 --> 41:21.609
If anything ever happens
to me, it's my mother.

41:21.653 --> 41:23.611
It's her fault."

41:23.655 --> 41:25.613
Kill her?

41:25.657 --> 41:29.965
Could Lucy Sable's mother
be a suspect in her murder?

41:30.009 --> 41:31.880
CELIA:
Everett's in custody.

41:31.924 --> 41:34.274
Carson knows enough
to keep him in there forever,

41:34.317 --> 41:38.278
so I want you to make sure
that Carson doesn't talk.

41:38.321 --> 41:41.368
No. Permanently.

41:41.411 --> 41:44.197
I want his daughter
to get our message, too.

41:44.240 --> 41:49.376
♪ If the moon is on time tonight ♪

41:49.419 --> 41:53.685
♪ Then they may be alone ♪

42:17.752 --> 42:19.711
[woman screams, bell dings]

42:19.754 --> 42:21.713
[pencil scribbling]
